        "content": "The factorial of a number n (denoted as n!) is the product of all positive integers from n down to 1. For 5, the factorial is calculated as follows:\n\n1. Write out the product: 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1.\n2. Multiply step by step:\n   - First, 5 × 4 = 20.\n   - Next, 20 × 3 = 60.\n   - Then, 60 × 2 = 120.\n   - Finally, 120 × 1 = 120.\n3. So, 5! = 120.\n\nThus, the factorial of 5 is 120.",
